                              <condition key="good">
                                The boards are splitted in two halves, repaired with metal wire and nails. While creating the holes into the boards for the wire, the bookbinder pierced the bifolia too, until fol. 14.
                                Tears on the parchment has been repaired during the manufacture process using a thread of vegetal origin. The flash side is not well scraped.
                              </condition>

